toxicity:
Highly toxic to humans and pets if ingested;
 contains calcium oxalate crystals that cause intense oral/throat swelling and burning
 (the "dumb cane" name comes from temporary loss of speech if chewed)

Mildly toxic to pets (cats, dogs, horses) if ingested due to saponins, causing vomiting/diarrhea; 
the inner gel is safe for topical human use and limited edible use, but the outer leaf latex (aloin) 
Is toxic if ingested in quantity
